<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource="User" Background="White" Name="flowDoc"
xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
xmlns:misc="clr-namespace:Cryptool.PluginBase.Miscellaneous;assembly=CrypPluginBase">
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16" xml:lang="de-de">
            <Span.TextDecorations>
                <TextDecoration Location="Underline" />
            </Span.TextDecorations> Using the "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">This plugin simulates three attacks against the secret key, which is used within the</Span>
        <Span FontStyle="Italic" xml:lang="de-de">Wired Equivalent Privacy</Span>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">(WEP) protocol for encryption and decryption (for a short intoduction into this WEP protocol, please have a
            look at the description tab of the "WEP protocol" plugin). The three attacks are the</Span>
        <misc:DescriptionHyperlink NavigateUri="http://www.drizzle.com/~aboba/IEEE/rc4_ksaproc.pdf">"FMS attack"</misc:DescriptionHyperlink>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">,</Span>
        <misc:DescriptionHyperlink NavigateUri="http://www.netstumbler.org/f50/aircrack-yet-another-wep-cracking-tool-linux-11878/index2.html">"KoreK attack"</misc:DescriptionHyperlink>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">and the</Span>
        <misc:DescriptionHyperlink NavigateUri="http://eprint.iacr.org/2007/120.pdf">"PTW attack"</misc:DescriptionHyperlink>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">: three different attacks with different fundamentals and different probabilities of success.</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">You can choose the attack either in the</Span>
        <Span FontStyle="Italic" xml:lang="de-de">Algorithm Settings</Span>
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">(within the drop down menu "Kind of attack"):</Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="190" Height="190" Source="/WEPAttacks;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/AtotWEPp_AS_KOA.jpg"/>
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">or by right clicking on the plugin in the editor:
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="240" Height="170" Source="/WEPAttacks;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/AtotWEPp_rightClick_KOA.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">If this plugin has been successful with the selected attack, you will be informed about
            this in the "QuickwatchPresentation" area:</Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="315" Height="419" Source="/WEPAttacks;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/AtotWEPp_QP_SUC.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">and in the message area at the bottom of the screen.</Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">There are a few more things in the "QuickwatchPresentation" area. The first line shows
            you if an attack is currently running, and, if an attack is running, which one it is (e.g. in the image above,
            the "FMS attack" is running). The second line shows how many packets has been read by this plugin ("Sniffed
            packets").
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The third line shows you, how many packets have been used for the analysis
            ("Used packets"). The "FMS attack" and also the "KoreK attack" uses only some special encrypted data packets.
            The "FMS attack" searches for special Initialisation Vectors (IV), the "KoreK attack" has some additional
            conditions, which decide wheather the packet is used for analysis or not. Within the "PTW attack", every packet
            is used for the analysis.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The text box within the "QuickwatchPresentation" area shows you the current state of the
            analysis. The first column is the number of the keybyte (beginning at "00"), and the following columns are
            the potential keybytes with their corresponding ranking in brackets. If you choose to run a "PTW attack", the
            presentation within this text box is a bit different. There are no columns any more, but one line, in which
            the currently most voted value for each keybyte is shown. So, the first value represents the potential first
            key byte, the second value the potential second keybyte and so on.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The keybytes are allways shown in hexadecimal notation. If the key has been reconstructed
            successfuly, this key will be presented to you in the normal ASCII notation, too.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">Now let's have a look on how you can use this plugin. It's part
            of a prepared workspace, which you can find in the CrypTool 2.0 SampleProjects folder. It's called
            "AttackWEP-01.cte" and provides the following workflow:
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
    
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The packets, which are created from the "Internet frame generator" plugin (IFG),
            are delivered to the "WEP protocol" plugin, which encrypts the packets according to the WEP protocol.
            This encrypted packets are then delivered to this "Attacks on the WEP protocol" plugin, which
            simulates the selected attack against the key, which has been used for encryption.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The following plugins are involved in the chain (besides the above mentioned
            ones): The "TextInput" plugin, the "Number Input" plugin, the "Multiplexer" plugin and the
            "IncDec" plugin. The "TextInput" provides the key for the "WEP protocol" plugin.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Width="522" Height="266" Source="/WEPAttacks;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/SW_AWEP.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">The packets, which are encrypted within the "WEP protocol" plugin, are then
            delivered to this plugin. It tries to recover the key, which has been used for the encryption.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">If the recovery of this key has not been successful with the number of packets
            adjusted in the IFG plugin, this plugin provides the value "false" at one of it's output. This
            value goes to the "Multiplexer" plugin, which decides whether the number provided by the "IncDec"
            plugin will be forwarded or not. If the value, provided by this plugin, is "false", the
            "Multiplexer" plugin will forward the incremented integer value. This incremented value is also
            forwarded to the IFG plugin, which will then create the requested packet in the requested amount
            once again. If the value provided from this plugin is "true", the "Multiplexer" plugin will
            forward nothing, and the chain stops working.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">So this workflow is a loop, which doesn't stop until the key has been recovered
            successful.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>